<h5 id="basic">The basics</h5>
<p>By default, the <code>tool-tip</code> component renders a <code>span</code> span element and uses the <code>title</code> attribute to derive tip content. This makes it easy to include tooltips within a paragraph of text. The display content which acts as the trigger for the tooltip can either come from the yield block of that component, or from its <code>text</code> attribute, making it possible to define tips in a very compact fashion.</p>

<div class="card">
    <div class="card-block">
        <p class="card-text">The quick brown {{#tool-tip title="who is quick and brown"}}fox{{/tool-tip}} jumped over the lazy dog.</p>
        <p class="card-text">The quick brown {{tool-tip text="fox" title="who is quick and brown"}} jumped over the lazy dog.</p>
    </div>
</div>

