<h5 id="icon">As an icon</h5>
<p>Tooltips are also often used to annotate "help" or "more information" iconography. To tip-ify an icon, simply add the required class names to the component from your typography library of choice. Here we are using Font Awesome. If the component has neither a yield block or text content to display, its <code>aria-hidden</code> attribute will be set in order to preserve accessibility of the page.</p>

<div class="card">
    <div class="card-block">
        <p class="card-text">This sentence leaves a great many things unclear. {{tool-tip class='fa fa-question-circle' title='And this tooltip is not particularly helpful either.'}}</p>
    </div>
</div>

